    {
      "number": 2,
      "title": "反问句 — Rhetorical Questions",
      "explanation": "A rhetorical question (反问句) is used to express a strong statement through a question form. Common patterns include: 你不知道吗？(Don't you know?) and 难道...吗？ (Could it be that...?). The speaker already knows the answer and uses the question to emphasize a point or express surprise.",
      "examples": [
        {
          "chinese": "书放在桌上，你没看见吗？",
          "pinyin": "Shū fàng zài zhuō shàng, nǐ méi kàn jiàn ma?",
          "english": "The book is on the table; didn't you see it?"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "这么简单，你不会吗？",
          "pinyin": "Zhè me jiǎn dān, nǐ bú huì ma?",
          "english": "It's so simple; you can't do it?"
        }
      ],
      "exercises": [
