    {
      "number": 3,
      "title": "连词「还是」— Conjunction haishi (or / either...or...)",
      "explanation": "还是 (háishi) means 'or' in questions and expresses a choice between two alternatives. Formula: A + 还是 + B? (Is it A or is it B?). Note: 还是 is used in questions asking for a choice, while 或者 (huòzhě) is used in statements. Example: 你喝茶还是喝咖啡？(Do you drink tea or coffee?)",
      "examples": [
        {
          "chinese": "你去还是不去？",
          "pinyin": "Nǐ qù hái shì bù qù?",
          "english": "Are you going or not?"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "你坐着等还是站着等？",
          "pinyin": "Nǐ zuò zhe děng hái shì zhàn zhe děng?",
          "english": "Are you waiting sitting down or standing up?"
        }
      ],
